Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, departed for the United States, 
where he is supposed to take part in the ceremony to sign the 
agreement on the creation of the Bosniak-Croatian federation in 
Washington on Friday [18 March]. In the presence of U.S. 
President Clinton, Croatian President Franjo Tudjman is also 
expected to place his signature on this agreement. 

